nginx.content:
- **Latest Version**: Check the official [Nginx website](https://nginx.org/en/download.html) for the latest version.

- **Installation**:
  ```bash
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install nginx
  ```

- **Key Configuration Options**:
  - `http`: The top-level block that contains all other configuration directives.
  - `server`: Defines a virtual server.
  - `location`: Specifies the location of requests to be handled by the server.

- **Rate Limiting**:
  ```nginx
  http {
      limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=one:10m rate=1r/s;

      server {
          location / {
              limit_req zone=one burst=5 nodelay;
          }
      }
  }
  ```

- **Reverse Proxy**:
  ```nginx
  server {
      listen 80;
      server_name example.com;

      location / {
          proxy_pass http://backend_server;
      }
  }
  ```

- **Load Balancing**:
  ```nginx
  upstream backend {
      server backend1.example.com;
      server backend2.example.com;
  }

  server {
      listen 80;
      server_name example.com;

      location / {
          proxy_pass http://backend;
      }
  }
  ```

- **Caching**:
  ```nginx
  http {
      proxy_cache_path /var/cache/nginx levels=1:2 keys_zone=my_cache:10m max_size=1g inactive=60m use_temp_path=off;

      server {
          location /static/ {
              alias /data/www/static/;
              expires 30d;
              add_header Cache-Control "public";
          }

          location /dynamic/ {
              proxy_pass http://backend;
              proxy_cache my_cache;
              proxy_cache_valid 200 301 302 10m;
              proxy_cache_valid any 1m;
          }
      }
  }
  ```

- **SSL/TLS**:
  ```nginx
  server {
      listen 443 ssl;
      server_name example.com;

      ssl_certificate /path/to/certificate.pem;
      ssl_certificate_key /path/to/privatekey.pem;

      location / {
          proxy_pass http://backend;
      }
  }
  ```

- **Logging**:
  ```nginx
  http {
      log_format main '$remote_addr - $remote_user [$time_local] "$request" '
                      '$status $body_bytes_sent "$http_referer" '
                      '"$http_user_agent" "$http_x_forwarded_for"';

      access_log /var/log/nginx/access.log main;
      error_log /var/log/nginx/error.log warn;
  }
  ```

- **Restart Nginx**:
  ```bash
  sudo systemctl restart nginx
  ```

- **Check Status**:
  ```bash
  sudo systemctl status nginx
  ```
